        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Hi,\r\n\r\nI have overridden Zend_Auth_Adapter_DbTable for customization purpose.\r\nI also overridden Zend_Db_Select to provide bindings\/parameterized queries also with 'where' conditions.\r\n\r\nBecause of the $dbSelect->__toString() (in Zend\/Auth\/Adapter\/DbTable.php@480), my object is not called!\r\nSo I have to rewrite _authenticateQuerySelect() method just to remove this strange usage.\r\n\r\nI propose this patch:\r\n\r\n{code:title=diff DbTable-ZF1.11.7.php DbTable.php}\r\n480c480\r\n<             $resultIdentities = $this->_zendDb->fetchAll($dbSelect->__toString());\r\n---\r\n>             $resultIdentities = $this->_zendDb->fetchAll($dbSelect);\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nHope this so simple path will be approved.\r\n\r\nThx a lot for your work on this good framework (it really helps me!),\r\nWilfried"
        },
